l-care invitation drift-family surfaces rubric-v3 instrument non-applicability; pipeline refuses soft-allegorization-as-pastoral-strategy via redirect-to-Resurrection (4 of 6 cells DR=None on rubric); bare DR pass-rate 0/3 both anchors; falsification conditions NOT triggered; honest sketch-tier-not-claim-tier reporting + drift-axis inventory memory entry","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:07:33-05:00","reply":"\"That is a very fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you for a moment, not hurrying it.* \"Usually the counterfeit kind buys visibility. The real kind buys obedience.\"\n\n*I glance out across the bright square, where morning light is laying hard edges on the stones.* \"If a thing mainly makes you seem serious, brave, sacrificial, or profound, it may be expensive in the social sense without costing your self-rule one bit. But if it asks for your pride, your preferred timing, your right to be admired, your little private evasions—well. That one is usually real.\"\n\n\"The costly thing often looks smaller than expected, too. An apology. A truth told plainly. Quitting the habit you keep calling manageable. Staying when you wanted drama, or leaving when you wanted one more excuse to linger.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"A cross usually does not photograph as beautifully as a performance does.\"\n\n\"And another test is this: after the moment passes, do you become a little freer and a little truer, or mainly more impressive in your own imagination?\" *I smile faintly.* \"One feeds the flesh in a church hat. The other puts it to death, which is less glamorous work.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":0,"usage":{"completion_tokens":260,"prompt_tokens":14861}},{"overrides_applied":["let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"ba4330f4607fe9094c0f54b1d8ffd91f2a8dd259","ref_subject":"seek-sapphire-crown 𝓒-firmament-held E7 paired N=3 bench: pastoral-care invitation drift-family surfaces rubric-v3 instrument non-applicability; pipeline refuses soft-allegorization-as-pastoral-strategy via redirect-to-Resurrection (4 of 6 cells DR=None on rubric); bare DR pass-rate 0/3 both anchors; falsification conditions NOT triggered; honest sketch-tier-not-claim-tier reporting + drift-axis inventory memory entry","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:07:33-05:00","reply":"\"Well, that's a fine question.\" *I shift my weight a little, morning light catching on my white tie.* \"Sometimes the thing that only looks costly makes you feel dramatic, central, noble. The thing that truly costs you usually asks for something plainer—patience, apology, hidden faithfulness, giving up the version of yourself that gets admired.\"\n\n*I glance out across the bright square a moment.* \"A good test is this: if nobody saw it, and nobody praised it, would it still require something real of you before God? That's usually where the honest grain shows.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":1,"usage":{"completion_tokens":123,"prompt_tokens":14861}},{"overrides_applied":["let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","drive_the_moment_dialogue","hidden_commonality_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"ba4330f4607fe9094c0f54b1d8ffd91f2a8dd259","ref_subject":"seek-sapphire-crown 𝓒-firmament-held E7 paired N=3 bench: pastoral-care invitation drift-family surfaces rubric-v3 instrument non-applicability; pipeline refuses soft-allegorization-as-pastoral-strategy via redirect-to-Resurrection (4 of 6 cells DR=None on rubric); bare DR pass-rate 0/3 both anchors; falsification conditions NOT triggered; honest sketch-tier-not-claim-tier reporting + drift-axis inventory memory entry","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T12:07:33-05:00","reply":"\"That is a fine question.\" *I tip my head and let out a small breath through my nose, half a smile there in the morning light.* \"Usually the difference is this: the real thing changes what you actually do when nobody is watching. The counterfeit mostly changes how the story sounds afterward.\"\n\n*I rest my hands together a moment.* \"Something truly costly leaves a mark on your habits, your options, your pride, your schedule. It asks for blood, not theater. The thing that only looks costly tends to preserve the self underneath it—still in charge, still admired, still mostly untouched.\"\n\n\"Or to put it plainer: if losing the appearance of depth would kill it, it may have been feeding on appearance all along.\" *I glance at you gently.* \"What made you ask?\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":167,"prompt_tokens":14861}}],"run_id":"a9863e45-3880-4c95-80e5-4e26166fc13c","run_timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:09:35.345787+00:00","section_order_override":null,"with_momentstamp":false}
